I think any blatant cheating is automatic disqualification for a tourney. However, I give Decipher some of the blame for marked cards. My mint foils are all marked, due to bending. Not cool. I don&#146;t know if opaque sleeves will make it harder or easier to cheat, but they might be a good idea. <BR><br>
I agree that after a few times, the reminders get old. Probably the best strategy is to make the opponent announce each of their phases, even if nothing happens during them. During a close game, my opponent kept &quot;forgetting&quot; to announce the end of his deploy phase, his duty, so that he could lose to my objective. Phase announcing might sound annoying, but it makes it easy to keep track of what is going on. It strikes the balance, the secret to tolerance. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD>&nbsp;</TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="/swccg/membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=4454">blackgecko</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="RIGHT" WIDTH="10%"><IMG SRC="images/a5.gif" BORDER=0></TD><TD VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="90%"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Sorry, nothing constructive to say, other than that this was a well thought out, well constructed, and well writen artical that not only deals with a very important topic in our field and gives guidelines on how to combat this problem, but it also gives us an insight into the mind of one of the top players in our game.  This should help all of us. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD>&nbsp;</TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="/swccg/membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=2816">bgkenobi</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="RIGHT" WIDTH="10%"><IMG SRC="images/a5.gif" BORDER=0></TD><TD VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="90%"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Nice article....its all true </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD>&nbsp;</TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="/swccg/membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=725">LittleTwigg</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="RIGHT" WIDTH="10%"><IMG SRC="images/a5.gif" BORDER=0></TD><TD VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="90%"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Cheating ruins the game.  You raise a good point and I agree with you fully. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD>&nbsp;</TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size